node.text:
Iceland, known for its mesmerizing landscapes, is also considered as one of the cleanest countries in the entire world.

Nations are measured by the Environmental Performance Index (EPI), which evaluates the cleanliness of 180 countries based on 24 indicators, such as air and water quality. The latest study in 2018 ranked Iceland 11th place.

The country also aims to become carbon neutral by 2040 🌎
